.TH "devm_sigmadsp_init_i2c" 9 "devm_sigmadsp_init_i2c" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_sigmadsp_init_i2c \- Initialize SigmaDSP instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sigmadsp *" devm_sigmadsp_init_i2c
.BI "(struct i2c_client *client "  ","
.BI "const struct sigmadsp_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "const char *firmware_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
The parent I2C device
.IP "ops" 12
The sigmadsp_ops to use for this instance
.IP "firmware_name" 12
Name of the firmware file to load
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates a SigmaDSP instance and loads the specified firmware file.

Returns a pointer to a struct sigmadsp on success, or a \fBPTR_ERR\fP on error.
